description:
The 15th century was ready for change, and in this episode, we explore Martin Luther's discovery of the Bible, becoming a remarkable turning point in history. He was originally born in Germany into a humble home, and though he had no desire for personal fame, he unexpectedly transformed not just his own country, but the whole continent. 

To find out more information about Martin Luther read our extended article.
